message.content:
A Sealyham Terrier is a breed of small to medium-sized dog originally bred in Wales for hunting small game.
They have a sturdy, muscular build and a wiry, weather-resistant coat that can be all white or white with lemon, brown, or black patches.
Their head is rectangular in shape with a prominent brow and whiskers that add to their distinctive expression.
They have small, round, dark eyes that are set deep in their skull, and a short, stubby tail that is often docked.
Sealyham Terriers are known for their loyal and affectionate nature, and make excellent family pets.
They are often used in competitive dog shows, and also excel in activities such as agility and obedience training.
Because of their cute and friendly appearance, they have also been used in advertising and media campaigns.
